        <td width="34%"><br>
        <img src="images/Mailbox2.gif" alt="Mailbox" align="left" hspace="6" vspace="6" WIDTH="150" HEIGHT="127"></td>
        <td width="66%"><big><strong>Contacting the City of Berkeley via E-mail</strong></big><p>Below
          are some useful
        City of Berkeley e-mail addresses.&nbsp; Please respect the following
          guidelines:&nbsp;</td>
      </tr>
    </table>
    <ul>
      <li>Since the Internet is not a fully secure medium, it is inappropriate to send
        confidential or sensitive information via email.</li>
      <li>All email sent to City of Berkeley addresses should include the sender's
        name and contact information (email address and/or telephone number) at
        the beginning of the <b>message text</b>, in case the email header is
        lost. </li>
      <li>Please use upper and lower case letters. ALL CAPITALS READS LIKE SHOUTING! </li>
      <li>Sending e-mail is very simple compared to writing a traditional letter,
        which is why the City of Berkeley offers this service. However, all users are
        respectfully requested to keep correspondence brief , and to be
        patient awaiting a response.<br>
 </li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>Technical Issues</strong><br>
    We've added &quot;mailto:&quot; links for each email address listed below.
    However, some browsers may not support these links.<br>
    <br>
    If you experience problems with &quot;mailto:&quot; addresses in general, please contact
    your system administrator or Internet service provider.<br>
    <br>
    For questions, comments, and suggestions concerning this site, please direct email to
    <a href="mailto:webmanager@ci.berkeley.ca.us">webmanager@ci.berkeley.ca.us.</a><br>
 </p>
